              }
            ],
            "name": "Crossover Ancestry NPCs",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 52,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Several of the NPCs elsewhere in NPC Core can fit well in this group: Bleachling survivor (level 2), orc gamekeeper (level 4), tripkee camoufleur (level 2), tripkee scout (level 1), woodland scouts (level 8)",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "lesser cheetah's elixir",
                "aonid": 3302,
                "game-obj": "Equipment",
                "name": "lesser cheetah's elixir",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "minor elixir of life",
                "aonid": 3308,
                "game-obj": "Equipment",
                "name": "minor elixir of life",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Foraging for Fun and Fortune",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 52,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "For some, variety is the spice of life, as long as you're certain of the plant you've just plucked. In lieu of finding manufactured treasure in a natural setting, a GM might allow for certain herbs, flowers, and vegetables discovered in the wild to act as level 1 alchemical elixirs. For instance, the white flowers known as fairycups have a spicy flavor when nibbled on, granting the benefits of a lesser cheetah's elixir. A nutritious knotted longbean restores health like a minor elixir of life. Such foraged items last only 24 hours after being plucked and can't be sold.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Survival",
                "aonid": 49,
                "game-obj": "Skills",
                "name": "Survival",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Nature",
                "aonid": 43,
                "game-obj": "Skills",
                "name": "Nature",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "Lore",
                "aonid": 41,
                "game-obj": "Skills",
                "name": "Lore",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Knowledge Exploration",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 52,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "While Survival and Nature are crucial skills for any explorer, various Lore skills can also prove useful for any NPC adventuring in the wilderness and can be easily swapped to make the skill set more applicable. \n* Architecture Lore\n* Engineering Lore\n* Fishing Lore\n* Herbalism Lore\n* Hunting Lore\n* Mining Lore\n* Sailing Lore\n* Scouting Lore",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Follow the Expert",
                "aonid": 2625,
                "game-obj": "Actions",
                "name": "Follow the Expert",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Tips From The Guide",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "aonid": 236,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "NPC Core pg. 52",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "NPC Core",
                "page": 52,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "For the Follow the Expert exploration activity, an explorer is considered an expert from levels 1\u20136, a master from levels 7\u201314, and legendary from levels 15 or higher. You might allow PCs who Follow the Expert when led by an explorer to continue to add their level to the skill check for some time afterward: 1 hour if the explorer is an expert, 1 day for master, or 1 week for legendary. A character can have this benefit for only one skill at a time.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "NPC Core pg. 52",
              "aonid": 236,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "NPC Core pg. 52",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "NPC Core",
            "page": 52,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Explorers are often well-equipped and well-trained for any type of hazard and are eager to lead others into the wild.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
